    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-10-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-10-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="178"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d178">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Chargé <persName type="to">Fletcher</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,<date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-10-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 23, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 355.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of Mr.
                    Rockhill’s dispatch No. 714, of the 4th ultimo, in further relation to the
                    subject of the Chinese characters to be used by the local Chinese authorities in
                    stamping deeds for property purchased for missionary purposes in China.</p>
                <p>With the dispatch is inclosed a copy of the translation of a note from the
                    Chinese foreign office, by which it is agreed to stamp the deeds in the manner
                    suggested by the legation.</p>
                <p>The department is glad that the more unequivocal expression has been definitely
                    agreed upon.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Bacon.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
